metadata.name: Journal : 01 #1/6
metadata.description:
Sunday  
February 5th, 2023

Sunday is a slow day in our house, we usually stay in bed a bit longer. 
But, today is a sunny Sunday, it’s so warm and bright outside, so I decide to get up early. 

I made myself a cup of warm cappuccino and  light my cigarette (i wish it was weed, though.)  
Also eating my daughter chocolate bar is one of my favorite, lol! 

I always start my day by sitting on my desk and just doodling around, trying to get myself in the mood for the day, to do stuff around the house. 

I have this new knickknack on my desk.  
it’s a little blue and white house made of ceramic; my aunt gave this tiny house decoration to me a while ago. 

A little backstory of the tiny house, though. 
So, my aunt used to work as a stewardess for KLM Airlines and she got this little decoration from her company. This tiny house decoration actually not a decoration at all, it’s actually a juice bottle from the Netherlands.  
I find that really interesting. 

After a few hours doodling around I go outside to check on my plants with my dog, Sunday.  
Plants are doing great, they kept growing and growing. I love tending my plants because it calms me down
